From 143e64370488cc4786a3cbcfe481fdaf240b9626 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Olaf Mandel <o.mandel@menlosystems.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 19:07:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] QMetaCallEvent: restore id() method

The method was unintentionally removed in commit
fbfc38717e17b1ca65dae411fb6e318f7d3cbdf1: restore it.

The `id()` method was removed together with several other methods in
commit fbfc38717e17b1ca65dae411fb6e318f7d3cbdf1. These other methods
were all marked as deprecated and their eventual removal described in
commit f6211c079fa000c0d46b7912341f014669fa628a, but `id()` was not
mentioned.

While the method is unused in the Qt codebase itself, there are usecases
where outside projects want to read this information. One example would
be an event-filter that wants to debug the name of each called slot. For
those usecases, restore the `id()` method.

Pick-to: 6.11
Fixes: QTBUG-146014
Change-Id: I11d6b812a714f24793a636042675d79aa2913126
Reviewed-by: Thiago Macieira <thiago.macieira@intel.com>
---
 src/corelib/kernel/qobject_p.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/corelib/kernel/qobject_p.h b/src/corelib/kernel/qobject_p.h
index 031fef3c7bf6..1e0e1b5dbd19 100644
--- a/src/corelib/kernel/qobject_p.h
+++ b/src/corelib/kernel/qobject_p.h
@@ -366,6 +366,8 @@ class Q_CORE_EXPORT QMetaCallEvent : public QAbstractMetaCallEvent
 
     virtual void placeMetaCall(QObject *object) override;
 
+    int id() const { return d.method_offset_ + d.method_relative_; }
+
 protected:
     struct Data {
         QtPrivate::SlotObjUniquePtr slotObj_;
